<br>
Well, there is some truth to that.  I don't think VI gives a crap about account selling.  By making the rules the way they did, they are simply trying to limit their own liability, and so that they don't have to deal with the CS issues.<br>
<br>
But if you want to bring the discussion to the level of 'Which rules are meant to be followed, and which are just there and its OK to break' is another issue entirely.<br>
<br>
I won't say I have never slipped a few miles over the posted MPH on the highway, but I won't complain that I got caught in a speed trap either.<br>
<br>
If you buy an EQ CD, and register an account, that account is recognized by VI as yours, and is non-transferrable.  Everyone knows that.  So if you 'sell' it to someone, as far as VI is concerned you violated the rules, and the punishment is having the account banned if you get caught.  The 'sale' itself is completely irrelevant.  I can offer to sell you Mars as well, but that doesn't mean its a legit sale if you give me money.<br>
<br>
Go to the Cops if you want to press charges for fraud / Con scheme but as far as the actual 'transaction' it is null and void.<br>
<br>
